Source: Xinhua News Agency, Sat 11 Sep 2004 [edited]
<http://www.xinhuanet.com/english/index.htm>

Zambia: Rabies Outbreak in Central Province; 2 Deaths
-----------------------------------------------------
An outbreak of rabies in the Central Province of Zambia has claimed 2
lives, Zambia News Agency reported on Fri 10 Sep 2004. Central
Province Permanent Secretary Richard Salivaji confirmed the deaths of
2 people who were bitten by a rabid dog in Kapiri Mposhi.
About 15 people are receiving treatment in Serenje district after a
rabid dog bit them on Thursday, while an undisclosed number of people
have been admitted to a health center in Kapiri Mposhi district.
Salivaji, who rushed to the district, said the government was
concerned about continuous reports of a rabies outbreak in the
province. However, he said that measures [canine vaccination] have
since been put in place to prevent further outbreaks of the disease.
